Sentencas: During the sintering process of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), the mismatch in the thermophysical properties of materials can lead to excessive local thermal stress and warpage.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: By establishing a 3D multiphysics model, the stress distribution and displacement during sintering are studied.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that when the anode and electrolyte thicknesses are 0.2 mm and 0.02 mm, respectively, the maximum sintering stress is 38.8 MPa, which is 48% lower than the maximum value of all simulation results.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, when the anode thickness is 0.7 mm and the electrolyte thickness is 0.008 mm, the maximum warpage displacement is the smallest at 0.14 mm.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A sintering preparation method for partially coated cells is proposed.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results can be used to optimize the sintering process of SOFCs and greatly reduce the sintering stress and warpage of SOFCs.
Titulo: Simulation and analysis of sintering stress and warpage displacement in anode supported planar solid oxide fuel cells
